            <entry xml:id="entry_allon" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d1233e66" type="lemma"><orth>allon</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d1233e69"><def xml:lang="ru">этнический термин, встречается только в сказках, в
                        выражении, вкладываемом обычно в уста великана-людоеда: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1233e72" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                            <w>am allon-billōny smag cæwy</w></mentioned></def><def xml:lang="en">an
                        ethnic term, found only in fairy tales, in an expression usually put into
                        the mouth of a cannibal giant: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1233e78" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                            <w>am allon-billōny smag cæwy</w></mentioned>.</def></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp xml:id="exampleGrp_d1233e84">
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1233e86">
                        <quote>sæ īw ū allon, se ʽnnæ ū billon</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>один из них — аллон, другой — биллон</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>one of them is allon, the other is billon</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>86</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1233e105">
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">иногда <hi rendition="#rend_italic">allon</hi> встречается и
                            самостоятельно, без <hi rendition="#rend_italic">billon</hi>: </note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">sometimes <hi rendition="#rend_italic">allon</hi> alone, without
                            <hi rendition="#rend_italic">billon</hi>: </note>
                        <quote>…fælæ wæm allony smag cæwy</quote>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            82</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Термин <hi rendition="#rend_italic">allon</hi> представляет безупречное с фонетической стороны
                    осетинское оформление <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e215" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e123" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>āryana</w>
                        <gloss><q>арийский</q></gloss></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e223" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e131" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>airyana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e228" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e136" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ārya-</w></mentioned>; переход <hi rendition="#rend_italic">r</hi> в <hi rendition="#rend_italic">l</hi> перед <hi rendition="#rend_italic">у</hi> закономерен для
                    осетинского (<bibl><author>Аndrеаs.</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Verhandlungen d. XIII Orient. Kongresses, стр.
                            103</biblScope></bibl>; см. также: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gramm._sogd."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">I стр.
                            III</biblScope></bibl>),
                    ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_mælyn"/> и др.; двойное <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ll</hi> — результат
                    ассимиляции (<hi rendition="#rend_italic">ry</hi> → <hi rendition="#rend_italic">II</hi>), ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_Wacilla"/> (из
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Wac-Ilia</hi>), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dællag"/> и др.; <hi rendition="#rend_italic">allon</hi>
                    предполагает с необходимостью более старую форму *<hi rendition="#rend_italic">allan</hi> (переход <hi rendition="#rend_italic">а</hi> в
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">о</hi> перед носовыми произошел относительно поздно, см.: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>256</biblScope></bibl>), т. е. мы
                    приходим к известному этническому термину алан (<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e254" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e162" xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>άλανοι</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e259" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e167" xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>Alani</w></mentioned>), названию средневекового народа на Северном
                    Кавказе, исторические связи которого с современными осетинами можно считать
                    прочно установленными (см.: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Миллер_Вс._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 39—66</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><author>Ю.
                            Кулаковский</author><biblScope>Аланы</biblScope></bibl>…). В <hi rendition="#rend_bold">мегр</hi>.
                    термин <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e273" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e181" xml:lang="xmf"><lang/>
                        <w>alani</w></mentioned> удержался до наших дней; он перенесен преемственно
                    на новых насельников аланской территории, карачаевцев, и значит, кроме того,
                    ‘удалец’, ‘герой’. Этот же этнический термин, воспринятый как социальный,
                    отложился, возможно, в <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e278" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e186" xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>alæ</w>
                        <gloss><q>князь</q></gloss></mentioned>. Без суффикса -<hi rendition="#rend_italic">on</hi>(← -<hi rendition="#rend_italic">an</hi>)
                    элемент <hi rendition="#rend_italic">al</hi>(← <hi rendition="#rend_italic">arya</hi>) наличен, по-видимому, в названиях божеств
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Kurd-Al-Wærgon</hi> → <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Kurdalægon</hi> ‘бог-кузнец’ и <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Borxwar-Ali</hi> ‘божество
                    проса’, а также в <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e286" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e194" xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>Ἀλήξαρθος</w></mentioned>. Что касается ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ir"/> ‘осетины’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_iron"/>
                    ‘осетин’, то они связываются с <hi rendition="#rend_italic">arya</hi> и Ираном по недоразумению. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ir"/>, а также <ref type="xr" target="#entry_Asy"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>245—247, 28,
                            48, 156, 214</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The term <hi rendition="#rend_italic">allon</hi> represents phonetically impeccable Ossetic
                    version of <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e123" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e215" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>āryana</w>
                        <gloss><q>Aryan</q></gloss></mentioned>, cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e131" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e223" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>airyana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e136" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e228" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ārya-</w></mentioned>; transition <hi rendition="#rend_italic">r</hi> to <hi rendition="#rend_italic">l</hi> before <hi rendition="#rend_italic">у</hi> is regular
                    for Ossetic (<bibl><author>Аndrеаs.</author><biblScope xml:lang="en">Verhandlungen d. XIII Orient.
                            Kongresses, p. 103</biblScope></bibl>; see also: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gramm._sogd."/><biblScope xml:lang="en">I p. III</biblScope></bibl>),
                    cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_mælyn"/> etc.; double <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ll</hi> is the result of
                    assimilation (<hi rendition="#rend_italic">ry</hi> → <hi rendition="#rend_italic">II</hi>), cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_Wacilla"/>
                    (from <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Wac-Ilia</hi>), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dællag"/> etc.; <hi rendition="#rend_italic">allon</hi>
                    necessarily assumes an older form *<hi rendition="#rend_italic">allan</hi> (transition <hi rendition="#rend_italic">а</hi> into <hi rendition="#rend_italic">о</hi> before
                    nasals happened relatively late, see: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>256</biblScope></bibl>), in other words, we come to a known
                    ethnic name for Alans (<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e162" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e254" xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>άλανοι</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e167" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e259" xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>Alani</w></mentioned>), the name of a medieval people in the North
                    Caucasus, whose historical connections with modern Ossetians can be considered
                    firmly established (see: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Миллер_Вс._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 39—66</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><author>Ю.
                            Кулаковский</author><biblScope>Аланы</biblScope></bibl>…). In
                    <hi rendition="#rend_bold">Mingrelian</hi> the term <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e181" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e273" xml:lang="xmf"><lang/>
                        <w>alani</w></mentioned> has been kept to this day; it was transferred
                    successively to the new inhabitants of the Alanian territory, the Karachays, and
                    therefore, in addition, it means a ‘brave’, ‘a hero’. The same ethnic term,
                    perceived as social, remained, possibly in <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e186" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e278" xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>alæ</w>
                        <gloss><q>prince</q></gloss></mentioned>. Without suffix -<hi rendition="#rend_italic">on</hi>(← -<hi rendition="#rend_italic">an</hi>)
                    the element <hi rendition="#rend_italic">al</hi>(← <hi rendition="#rend_italic">arya</hi>) is found apparently in deities' names:
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Kurd-Al-Wærgon</hi> → <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Kurdalægon</hi> ‘god-blacksmith’ and <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Borxwar-Ali</hi> ‘millet
                    deity’, and also in <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d1233e194" xml:id="mentioned_d1233e286" xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>Ἀλήξαρθος</w></mentioned>. As for Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ir"/> ‘Ossetians’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_iron"/>
                    ‘Ossetiam’, these terms are connected with <hi rendition="#rend_italic">arya</hi> and Iran by mistake. See
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ir"/>, and also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_Asy"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>245—247, 28, 48, 156, 214</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
